    "en": {
      "title": "The gangster who fled in the midst of police fire was arrested",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Kaduwela police said that three people in the luxury jeep who fled amid the firing by the station commander of the Kaduwela police were arrested last night with sharp weapons and drugs.",
        "Police have taken into custody a knife, three swords, and five stolen drugs in the possession of the suspects. Inspector Kan Weerasinghe, Station Commander of the Kaduwela Police, was returning to the police station from the annual procession of the idols at the Kaduwela Rankadu Pattini temple, when he saw several people hurriedly get out of a luxury jeep parked in front of a petrol station in Kaduwela town. The police say that there was.",
        "On seeing the police car, the group turned back and ran to the jeep they came in and got into it. The station commander got out of the car and pointed the pistol at the jeep and shouted for it to stop. The police say that they were attacked.",
        "However, in the middle of the gunfire, the police team, including the station commander, chased the group to a distance of eight hundred meters from the jeep and got out of it on a side road.",
        "During the lengthy interrogation of the arrested suspects, it has been stated that they came prepared to attack the house of a drug dealer in Kaduwela area and that they got down from the jeep with sharp weapons after seeing the drug dealer coming forward on a motorcycle.",
        "The station commander said that a special police team has been deployed to find the suspect who fled at that time. The arrested suspects are residents of Ranala and Kaduwela and are between the ages of 26 and 38. Kaduwela Police Station Commander Inspector Kan Weerasinghe said that two of the drug-trafficking suspects were recently released on bail from prison. All the suspects are to be produced before the Kaduwela Courts"
      ],
